    "liner_notes": "Critics hated it. Columbia didn't understand it. But *On the Corner* was Miles firing a flare into the future. Conceived as a response to Sly Stone and James Brown, designed to reach young Black audiences, it was assembled by Teo Macero from hours of studio improvisation. Cyclical, polyrhythmic, relentless — it has no parallel in the jazz canon.",
